I can always count on octane for a great meal! Some of my fav options are: Mac n cheese, fried chicken bao (appetizer), bleu note burger, shrimp pompano, tacos, ridge runner - basically everything on the menu is GOOD and whatever you choose you will not be disappointed! They also have a cocktail menu, tons of beer and wine to choose from.

Been going to this place since they accidentally left the front door unlocked a week before they opened.  If there's only one place to stop for a coffee, cocktail, or meal in Rockford, this is it.  I suggest a house coffee, a blue smurf, or a Japanese Orchid (not that those are always on the menu) and pretty much any noodle, seafood, or burger that catches your eye.  I've literally NEVER had a bad plate there.  Just realize the locals know this place and pack it full, so be prepared for a short wait for a table. (....which is a perfect time for a drink!)

We were told this place was great to hit before going a show at the Coronado. There is a huge variety of chooses right around the building. Parking is limited, so plan for Street parking. We got a table but I advise making reservations. The establishment isn't very big and if there is a show going on it'll be busy. Most of the tables are 2 or 4 people. They have a full bar and a nice selection of beers and cocktails. The service was pretty slow and took us about 15mins before someone took our drink order. By then we knew our dinner choices. The drinks again took quite a while to come, 10mins more. Mind you it REALLY wasn't that busy, most tables were empty. It seemed like there were only 2 guys working the entire place. The food did come out hot and beautiful presentation. The burger was done to perfection, the potato. Wedges were 'wigwammed' stacked. My Father Knows Best turkey on sourdough was excellent. Choose the Cesar salad, it was wonderful. I'd got back, Knowing I'd have a slow, time to relax meal.

I love Octane but was very disappointed tonight. Ordered the twisted mac which has chicken in it. There was no chicken in the dish. I told our waitress and she was apologetic and said she would take care of it. Instead of remaking our dish she returned to our tablet with room temperature chicken to add to our now room temperature twisted Mac. She asked if everything was ok and I informed her that I was disappointed that the dish was not remade at which time she said she would discount the price. The discount was $2.25!!!  It will take a while before I will return.  Feel sad because I love Octane. 😞. Prior to tonight 5 stars all day long!!!😊

The atmosphere was great!!! Art on the walls, soft lighting, very clean restrooms & great wait staff as far as being polite, but not very informative.  The food however was not as good as it should have been for the pricing. We ordered a Mushroom soup which was amazing,, nachos which I just assumed came with meat, but didn't, the chese was overly spicy, there were peppers everywhere, but it was not worth the price, Although the waitress was nice I wished she had given me more information because it was my first time there.  My sister ordered the noodles, which had a great flavor, but they were undercooked, so instead of offering her a new order, because they were $13.00, the waitress took the bowl and said, "i'll.have the cook just throw them on a little longer.  My niece & sister say that the food was really good & maybe it normally is, but for the pricing I expected much more.  I'm really passive, so I didn't say anything, and although I wanted desert, wasn't willing to spend more money to be disappointed.  Overall, the food was overpriced for the quality of the meal, the undercooked noodles, just seems for $13.00 a new order would have been appropriate.  When I ordered nachos, didn't know it was without meat, but when I asked for chicken, the waitress should have mentioned it was an extra $4 or $5 for a few chunks of chicken.  I like to try new restaurants & enjoy a night out twice a month, but I was disappointed.

Octane is the best place for fun drinks with your friends, a classy dinner before a theater or music experience, a celebration with family, a lunch meeting with a colleague or client and any other kind of situation you can think of. Whenever I bring guests to Octane for the first time they say "Wow I don't feel like I'm in Rockford right now." The environment and atmosphere is hip/retro/spacey/modern/fusion! In summer the patio is gorgeous and you can dine with your pup outside.  Waitstaff is always consistent and friendly, the kitchen and staff seem to operate like a well-oiled friendly machine. You can see that things are respectful and working with ultimate team work! The FOOD. IS. AMAZING. Great well rounded menu for meat eaters and vegetarians, nice wine selection, full barista capabilities, and the bartenders can make basically anything. Thanks Octane for being my favorite restaurant for 10+ years!

So we assumed since no one greeted us it was casual style seating, so we commenced to seating ourselves, the waitress behind the bar says, "umm what are you guys doing".  I ask politely to sit at the bar, and the waitress rolls her eyes. We were a group of 4 and the bar had seats for 7, 2 seats were taken, but in middle of the bar.  We just wanted to grab one seat from the left of the bar and bring it to the right of the bar so our group could sit together.  The bartender objected to this, told us we could not move the chair and sit together.... that was the last straw, my colleagues and i just went down the street to kryptonite and had an awesome night.

Perhaps it is because I relocated from a much larger city, but I found Octane's food to be merely adequate. I ordered the halibut with pureed sweet potatoes, chickpeas, and . . . zucchini (?) and carrots.  Zucchini seemed wildly out of place in this dish and didn't fare well palate-wise relative to the other flavors. My dining partner had the pasta du jour, which was wide noodles with red pepper and tons of mushrooms. The dish was extremely bland. The desserts were OK. Service was most certainly not attentive, yet the place was not at all packed with people.
